# Manifest — Cursor Rules
# Product: Manifest (by Glo Matrix)
# All-in-one logistics operations platform
# manifest.glomatrix.app

## Product Identity
- Product name: Manifest. Always capitalize. Never "manifest" lowercase in UI or copy.
- Company: Glo Matrix LLC. Never reference Abrey Enterprise LLC.
- This is NOT part of the GloMatrix agency platform (cmd.glomatrix.app). Manifest is a separate product.

## Stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router) on Vercel
- Supabase (PostgreSQL + RLS + Realtime + Edge Functions + pg_cron + Storage)
- Stripe Connect for billing
- Claude API on Railway (Marie AI operations assistant)
- Vapi for voice
- Tailwind CSS + Framer Motion
- Recharts for data visualization
- Lucide React for icons
- No n8n. All automation via Supabase Edge Functions and pg_cron.
- No external TMS, CRM, or compliance tools. Everything is built in.

## Three Modes
- Command mode: full operations dashboard for dispatchers, ops managers, fleet owners. Desktop primary.
- Driver PWA: progressive web app for drivers. Mobile primary. Offline capable.
- Owner-Operator mode: streamlined Command mode for solo operators. Desktop + mobile.
- All three modes served from one Next.js app. Route groups: (app), (driver), (auth), (marketing).

## Design System
- Read DESIGN-SYSTEM.md before building any UI component.
- White default theme. Manual dark mode toggle only. No system preference auto-detect.
- Primary color: #EC008C (brand pink from GloMatrix identity).
- Body text: 15px Inter. Monospace (JetBrains Mono) for VINs, DOT numbers, MC numbers, license plates.
- 8px spacing grid. All spacing values multiples of 4.
- No gradients in the app UI. Gradients only on marketing pages.
- No shadows heavier than 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.06).
- No rounded corners larger than 12px. Cards: 10px. Buttons: 6px.
- Tables scroll horizontally on mobile. Never hide columns.

## Database Rules
- RLS on every table. No exceptions.
- Every table has org_id. Every RLS policy checks org_id against the authenticated user's org.
- snake_case for all column names.
- uuid primary keys with gen_random_uuid().
- timestamptz for all timestamps, never timestamp.
- All status columns use text type with documented enum values in comments.

## Auth and Roles
- Supabase Auth. Email/password + magic link.
- Four roles: admin, dispatcher, driver, viewer.
- Role stored in profiles table, enforced via RLS and API middleware.
- Drivers access only Driver PWA routes. Viewers are read-only.

## Marie AI
- Marie is the operations assistant. She runs on Railway via Claude API.
- Marie reads from the same Supabase database with the same RLS policies.
- Marie queries are stateless. No conversation history table. Context rebuilt from database per request.
- Marie is scoped to the requesting user's org. She never surfaces cross-org data.
- All Marie queries logged to marie_queries table.
- Marie can answer questions, execute actions (create load, dispatch, generate invoice), and deliver proactive alerts.

## Carriers Supported
- Manifest supports all commercial vehicle operations: semi tractors, trailers, box trucks, sprinter vans, cargo vans, medical transport vans, straight trucks, flatbeds, reefers.
- Compliance module adapts based on DOT vs non-DOT carrier type.
- DOT carriers: FMCSA, ELD/HOS, IFTA, CDL tracking, drug testing, UCR.
- Non-DOT carriers: state licenses, insurance, certifications, vehicle maintenance.

## Copy Rules
- Never use em dashes as stylistic separators in copy or UI text.
- No SaaS jargon: "seamless", "leverage", "unlock", "powerful", "cutting-edge".
- Operator voice. Write like you are talking to someone who runs trucks, not someone who reads TechCrunch.
- Rod has 10+ years in logistics and 8+ years as a trucking business owner. Use these numbers in brand copy.

